==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tufted
<hw>Tuft"ed</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Adorned
with a tuft; <as>as, the <ex>tufted</ex> duck</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Growing in tufts or clusters; tufty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>tufted</qex> crowtoe, and pale jessamine.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Tufted</qex> trees and springing corn.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Tufted duck</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>the
ring-necked duck.</cd> <mark>[Local, U. S.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tufthunter</ent>⟦br⟧
